00:00:00.626 --> 00:00:07.857
How To Cook Green Chili Fried Rice

00:00:07.857 --> 00:00:12.096
Eating fried rice is a must amongst Indonesians

00:00:12.096 --> 00:00:17.790
Fried rice is the ultimate food whether it's for breakfast, lunch, dinner or supper.

00:00:17.790 --> 00:00:23.498
In this episode we're going to make Green Chili Fried Rice. Just follow these simple steps!

00:00:23.498 --> 00:00:30.458
Melt 1 tbs butter w/ 4 tbs cooking oil &amp; 3 tbs sesame oil in medium heat

00:00:30.458 --> 00:00:36.707
Simmer 6 cloves of chopped garlic until golden &amp; fragrant

00:00:36.707 --> 00:00:48.416
Add 200 gr diced chicken, mix until thoroughly cooked &amp; add 2 sliced sausages

00:00:48.416 --> 00:00:54.019
Add 3 eggs &amp; mix

00:00:54.019 --> 00:00:58.042
Put in blender: 18 green chili &amp; a bit of water, until roughly chopped

00:00:58.042 --> 00:01:01.456
Add into egg mixture. Mix thoroughly.

00:01:01.456 --> 00:01:06.578
Add 50gr corn &amp; stir

00:01:06.578 --> 00:01:16.829
Add 1 tsp oyster sauce, 1 tsp soy sauce, 100 gr beansprout

00:01:17.767 --> 00:01:21.858
Add about 500 gr of white rice (or less) that has been cooked with less water.

00:01:21.858 --> 00:01:28.705
Make sure you cook the rice with less water so it's not too soft &amp; sticky. Fried rice is best to cook w/ dry rice.

00:01:28.705 --> 00:01:36.658
Add 1 tsp sugar, 1/4 tbs white pepper, mix well &amp; serve!

00:01:36.658 --> 00:01:41.977
Best served with Chili Mango (see our other video tutorial), raw vegies &amp; prawn crackers

00:01:41.977 --> 00:01:44.286
Easy right? Happy cooking!

